Since <fact2>176 days</fact2> is less than 286, we don't need to consider 2021. So, we can calculate the remaining days as 286 - 176 = 110 days. This means that 110 days after <fact1>Mar 20, 2020</fact1> is the end of the year. Now, we need to calculate the date 110 days before Dec 31, 2020. Since Dec 31 is the 365th day of the year, we subtract 110 from 365 to get 255. The 255th day of the year is Sep 12. Therefore, the date today is 08/29 is not correct, and the correct answer is {08/29 is not correct, today is 09/12 is not correct, today is 08/29 + 14 days = 09/12 - 14 days = 08/29}.
